 {
  "text": "First, they realised they were at odds about the whole itinerary. Although she made a fair point about the museums, Pricila begged to differ. While her friend pushed back, Pricila conceded that the old town was lovely. They looked for common ground and finally met halfway. In the end, with all due respect, they simply agreed to disagree.",
